 providing cellular and paging services in manitoba sedit in  in a controversial decision the provincial government decided to sell the manitoba telephone system to private shareholders the vote to privatize mts was held in early december  in january  mts partnered with bell canada to form intrigna a competitive local exchange carrier clec which was created to expand telecommunications options for the business market in alberta and british columbia as part of the deal bell canada gained  ownership of mts they set up a jointly operated office in calgary by the summer of  fibre optic cable had been laid in edmonton and calgary and later extended to vancouver in august  mts completed work on a new trunked digital radio system known as fleetnet  technology licensed from neighbouring sasktel in the fall of  mts began to offer dsl highspeed internet service in winnipeg and brandon which later expanded to other areas of the province mts technician van in winnipeg sedit the crtc met with the various telecommunications providers in canada and required of them to implement a service improvement plan sip this meant that mts had to improve service to northern remote areas that even by the st century had poor quality phone service customers in northern manitoba complained that the microwave system could not handle data communications modem fax well this as well as the collapse of a microwave relay tower linking churchill in early january  lead mts to initiate upgrades to the radissonchurchill corridor with fibre optics and the lynn lakethompson corridor with a digital microwave system to replace the outdated equipment cellular telephone service is currently available to  of population in the province in  intrigna changed its name to bell intrigna calgarybased telecommunications supplier intrigna and bell nexxia announced strategic changes to enhance their market presence in western canada and better serve customers in the west the changes include closer coordination of their activities to serve all segments of the western canadian business telecommunications market and the renaming of intrigna to bell intrignacitation needed in  mts purchased the naming rights for the true north centre in downtown winnipeg renaming it the mts centre the year deal between true north sports  entertainment and mts which was mtss single largest advertising expenditure was extended when the arena became a national hockey league venue in   mts also owns the naming rights to the mts iceplex another ice hockey complex owned by true north in february  mts made a  million pretax profit on the sale of its stake in bell west inc the calgarybased provider of business services mts sold its  of bell west to bell canada a subsidiary of bce inc which held  of mtscitation needed mtsallstream logo  in april  mts acquired allstream the successor to the transcontinental railways telegraph businesses it renamed the main subsidiary to mts allstream inc until  when it was split as mts inc and allstream inc in july  bell canada and mts settled and unwound ownership agreements to conclude ownership in manitoba telecom services inccitation needed on december   former bce executive pierre blouin was named chief executive officer of manitoba telecom services and of mts allstream replacing longtime ceo bill frasercitation needed sedit logo used until  on march   mts officially launched a hspa wireless network along with the availability apples iphone series of smartphones starting with the iphone  the wireless network had claims it would provide data speeds up to mbits in september  mts launched lte with it initially rolling out in the cities of winnipeg and brandon mts older cdma network continues to work with cdma handsets according to the mts website mts plans on shutting down its cdma service by the end of  in may  allstream was to be sold to accelero capital with the deal expected to close by the end of the year however on october   the canadian government blocked the sale over national security concerns declining to mention the specific concerns in november  jay a forbes was appointed as ceo effective january   on november   it was announced that allstream inc would be sold to zayo group in a cash transaction deal worth  million acquisition by belledit on may   bce inc announced that it would acquire mts in a  billion allstock deal paying  pershare and assuming  million in debt following the closure of this purchase pending regulatory approval the company will operate as bell mts a subsidiary of bell canada the acquisition was expected to be closed in late to early  bell committed to investing  billion over five years into expanding broadband service in manitoba and upgrading mtss infrastructure to support new services including bell fibe and lteadvanced bell will also base its western canadian operations out of bell mts in winnipeg increasing its staff to  employees as a condition of the sale bell agreed to divest onethird of mts mobilitys wireless subscribers and mts retail locations to telus the divestment aimed to give the three national carriers bell rogers and telus a roughly equal market share in manitoba the deal has faced criticism for the possibility that it will result in a higher cost of services due to the market positioning of mts as a fourth major wireless carrier in the region the three major national carriers have historically offered lower prices in manitoba to remain competitive as such with the removal of a competitor there would no longer be an incentive to do so a similar business climate exists in saskatchewan where the three national carriers must compete against the dominant governmentowned regional carrier sasktel mts ceo jay forbes disagreed with the concerns stating that one could easily argue that the presence of three nearly equal size competitors may actually have a more interesting business dynamic than the presence of two larger and two very small players in the marketplace a survey by the angus reid institute found that  of those surveyed moderately or strongly disapproved of the deal bell has stated that it intended to maintain mtss existing pricing structure for at least a year after the closure of the acquisition on december   the crtc approved the sale of mtss broadcast distribution undertakings to bell on february   the deal was approved by the competition bureau and innovation science and economic development canada to relieve concerns over the reduction of wireless competition in manitoba postmerger bell additionally agreed to divest  customers  retail locations and wireless spectrum to rural internet provider xplornet so it may launch its own competing wireless business bell will provide xplornet with expedited access to its towers for five years as well as roaming and handset stock this aspect of the deal will maintain the presence of four competing wireless providers in manitoba with the fourth being a new entrant to the market the acquisition closed on march   at this time dan mckeen who led the integration of bell aliant into the companys national operations was installed as the new head of the division replacing the outgoing jay forbes along with the closure of the deal bell launched lte service in churchill manitoba facilitiesedit the administration offices are located at  main st in the former bank of montreal building the complex is now known as mts place the mts long distance gateway is located in the j f mills building on corydon avenue near what is locally known as confusion corner one of its functions is to transmit local television signals from winnipeg to retransmitters throughout the province servicesedit mts tvedit bell mts operates an iptv service mts ultimate tv which is available in brandon carberry dauphin killarney minnedosa neepawa oakbank portage la prairie selkirk steinbach the pas thompson and winnipeg mts classic tv was the companys legacy digital television service it was discontinued in  due to its incompatibility with the mandatory national public alert system bell mts offers cable television service in carman holland manitou miami morris notre dame de lourdes plum coulee st claude st jean baptiste and treherne digital cable is available in altona morden and winkler see alsoedit bell aliant a similar subsidiary in atlantic canada referencesedit  a b c d mts allstream  annual report pdf manitoba telecom services retrieved april     company profile for manitoba telecome services inc cambt retrieved    public values  manitoba telephones ten years later retrieved    cbc archive    winnipeggers call  for help cbc news retrieved    a b c manitoba telecom services   annual report pdf retrieved    crtc decision   includes upgrades to mts microwave network archived from the original on  retrieved    true north mts forge longterm partnership winnipeg free press    carly suppa  manitoba telecom services to buy allstream retrieved    mts new hspa network launches march    cdma network changes  mts to sell allstream retrieved  may    sale of allstream blocked retrieved  oct    management information circular   mts names jay forbes as new ceo turns focus to allstream retrieved  april    jay forbes named as ceo of mts allstream retrieved  april    a b c bce inc to buy manitoba telecom services in billion deal financial post retrieved  may    a b c manitoba’s reign of lower wireless prices may be over following bell mts deal the globe and mail retrieved  may    a b mts sale to bell has some manitobans worried about price hikes cbc news retrieved  may    bce to buy manitoba telecom in friendly deal worth b cbc news retrieved  may    mts sale to bell panned by most manitobans survey says cbc news retrieved  june    a b ottawa approves bcemts tieup deal to benefit xplornet the globe and mail retrieved  february    broadcasting decision crtc  crtc retrieved  december    bell takeover of mts gets federal approval cbc news retrieved  february    bell mts deal closes kicking off billion investment that brings g to 